Detailed Description

A class representing a rotation order.

Member Typedef Documentation

int DzRotationOrder::AxisOrder[3]

Order of the axes for Euler angle rotations to be applied in. This is just a different representation of rotation order and encapsulates the exact same information as the RotOrder type. The AxisOrder type is an array of three integers - each integer must be in the range [0,2] with no duplicates in order to be valid. This type is provided for convenience when it is necessary to iterate over the three axes in the order of rotation.

For Example:

  • 'DzRotationOrderRotOrder xyz=DzRotationOrderXYZ;' could also be represented by 'DzRotationOrderAxisOrder xyz={0,1,2};'
  • 'DzRotationOrderRotOrder yzx=DzRotationOrderYZX;' could also be represented by 'DzRotationOrderAxisOrder yzx={1,2,0};'
